This paper discusses the design principle and evaluation of algorithms for resource management in smart city applications, which involves human-centered measures such as privacy, fairness, and social welfare. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CY (Computers and Society), followed by cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction), and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
